pokedexEntries.red: The tentacles are normally kept short. On hunts, they are extended to ensnare and immobilize prey.
pokedexEntries.blue: The tentacles are normally kept short. On hunts, they are extended to ensnare and immobilize prey.
pokedexEntries.yellow: Its 80 tentacles can stretch and contract freely. They wrap around prey and weaken it with poison.
pokedexEntries.gold: Its 80 tentacles absorb water and stretch almost endlessly to constrict its prey and enemies.
pokedexEntries.silver: In battle, it extends all 80 of its tentacles to entrap its opponent inside a poisonous net.
pokedexEntries.crystal: When its 80 feelers absorb water, it stretches to become like a net to entangle its prey.
pokedexEntries.ruby: Tentacruel has large red orbs on its head. The orbs glow before lashing the vicinity with a harsh ultrasonic blast. This Pokémon's outburst causes rough waves around it.
pokedexEntries.sapphire: Tentacruel has tentacles that can be freely elongated and shortened at will. It ensnares prey with its tentacles and weakens the prey by dosing it with a harsh toxin. It can catch up to 80 prey at the same time.
pokedexEntries.emerald: It lives in complex rock formations on the ocean floor and traps prey using its 80 tentacles. Its red orbs glow when it grows excited or agitated.
pokedexEntries.fireRed: It has 80 tentacles that move about freely. They can sting, causing poisoning and sharp, stabbing pain.
pokedexEntries.leafGreen: The tentacles are normally kept short. On hunts, they are extended to ensnare and immobilize prey.
pokedexEntries.diamond: With 80 tentacles for ensnaring victims, it prevents escape until the prey is weakened by poison.
pokedexEntries.pearl: It alerts others to danger by stridently flashing the red orbs on its head.
pokedexEntries.platinum: It extends its 80 tentacles to form an encircling poisonous net that is difficult to escape.
pokedexEntries.heartGold: Its 80 tentacles absorb water and stretch almost endlessly to constrict its prey and enemies.
pokedexEntries.soulSilver: In battle, it extends all 80 of its tentacles to entrap its opponent inside a poisonous net.
pokedexEntries.black: It extends its 80 tentacles to form an encircling poisonous net that is difficult to escape.
pokedexEntries.white: It extends its 80 tentacles to form an encircling poisonous net that is difficult to escape.
pokedexEntries.black2: It extends its 80 tentacles to form an encircling poisonous net that is difficult to escape.
pokedexEntries.white2: It extends its 80 tentacles to form an encircling poisonous net that is difficult to escape.
pokedexEntries.x: The tentacles are normally kept short. On hunts, they are extended to ensnare and immobilize prey.
pokedexEntries.y: It has 80 tentacles that move about freely. They can sting, causing poisoning and sharp, stabbing pain.
pokedexEntries.omegaRuby: Tentacruel has large red orbs on its head. The orbs glow before lashing the vicinity with a harsh ultrasonic blast. This Pokémon's outburst creates rough waves around it.
pokedexEntries.alphaSapphire: Tentacruel has tentacles that can be freely elongated and shortened at will. It ensnares prey with its tentacles and weakens the prey by dosing it with a harsh toxin. It can catch up to 80 prey at the same time.
pokedexEntries.sun: Normally, it has 80 poisonous tentacles. The longer one has been alive, the fewer tentacles it will have.
pokedexEntries.moon: Although these Pokémon are rare, when a large outbreak of them occurs, all fish Pokémon disappear from the surrounding sea.
pokedexEntries.ultraSun: It fires off ultrasonic waves from its red orbs to weaken its prey, and then it wraps them up in its 80 tentacles.
pokedexEntries.ultraMoon: It communicates with others of its kind by lighting up the red orbs on its head. When the orbs are blinking, it’s a warning sign.
